The paper deals with the restoration of underwater images using compressed sensing and local polynomial image representations. The use of compressed sensing suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. However, the paper also deals with image restoration, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The paper also deals with motion estimation, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with numerical optimization, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the use of Fourier transforms, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
